\title{boldR: fMRI BOLD Signal Analysis for Circadian and Sleep Research}
\description{
\code{boldR} analyses Blood-Oxygen-Level-Dependent (BOLD) fMRI data in the
context of sleep and circadian research. It picks up exactly where
\href{https://fmriprep.org}{fMRIPrep} leaves off — working directly with
preprocessed BIDS derivatives — and transforms them into analysis-ready
outputs: atlas-agnostic parcellation, ROI-level timeseries, functional
connectivity matrices, and voxelwise quality metrics.

\strong{fmriprep gets you clean data. boldR gets you useful data.}
